We had a guild chat regarding loot rules the other night and I think we have come up with a nice, simple set of rules for a loot list.  <br>
<br>
The most important thing we can do is to get rules implemented as quickly as we can in order to appease the masses and get some fair looting going on.<br>
<br>
*********************<br>
<br>
Proposal:<br>
<br>
Create a loot list, by class.<br>
<br>
Initial order of list determined by randoming, with a couple of exceptions: Tabalar at top of druid list, Azerk to get first warrior BP that drops. (DS will probably have exceptions too, feel free to post 'em)<br>
<br>
Winners of loot drop to bottom of loot list.<br>
<br>
If a person does not show up to a raid, that person is frozen in their current loot list position for that raid.<br>
<br>
If a player plays two characters throughout the raid (dual boxing), the player is allowed loot list rank gains on both toons.  (Unless officers determine that one toon is &quot;dead weight&quot;)<br>
<br>
Players switching toons during the raid are allowed rank gains on only one toon.<br>
<br>
Multi class loot will be handled with a secondary list composed of class names.  The class at the top of the class list wins the multi class drop, with that class then dropping to the bottom of the list.<br>
<br>
Invites attend 2 raids to get on the loot list, with a couple notable exceptions:  Zoto and Tanori.<br>
<br>
Invites that have made the list, but then miss 7 consecutive raids will be dropped from the list.<br>
<br>
***********<br>
<br>
<br>
Please post your comments, both positive and negative, here by Friday, June 28th, so that we may implement loot rules as quickly as possible.<br>
<br>
